Configures Windows MDM auto-enrollment policies, triggers Microsoft Intune enrollment, and creates a scheduled enrollment task while generating detailed diagnostic logs.

Detailed Description

This PowerShell script automates Microsoft Intune MDM enrollment remediation by:

Creating a dedicated logging directory and timestamped log file.
Recording enrollment actions and diagnostic information throughout execution.
Capturing the current device registration state using:
dsregcmd /status
Configuring required MDM enrollment policy settings:
AutoEnrollMDM = 1
UseAADCredentialType = 1
Removing any existing enrollment task to avoid conflicts.
Creating a new scheduled task that runs:
deviceenroller.exe /c /AutoEnrollMDM
Running the enrollment process immediately without waiting for the scheduled task trigger.
Capturing scheduled task details after creation.
Generating a complete enrollment log for troubleshooting and audit purposes.




$LogDir = "C:\MDMLogs"

if (!(Test-Path $LogDir)) {
    New-Item -ItemType Directory -Path $LogDir -Force | Out-Null
}

$TimeStamp = Get-Date -Format "yyyyMMdd_HHmmss"
$LogFile = "$LogDir\MDM_Enroll_$TimeStamp.log"

function Write-Log {
    param([string]$Message)

    $Line = "$(Get-Date -Format 'yyyy-MM-dd HH:mm:ss') - $Message"
    Add-Content -Path $LogFile -Value $Line
    Write-Output $Line
}

Write-Log "====================================="
Write-Log "MDM Enrollment Script Started"
Write-Log "====================================="

Write-Log "Collecting dsregcmd status..."
dsregcmd /status | Out-File $LogFile -Append

Write-Log "Configuring AutoEnrollMDM..."
reg add "HKLM\SOFTWARE\Policies\Microsoft\Windows\CurrentVersion\MDM" /v AutoEnrollMDM /t REG_DWORD /d 1 /f 2>&1 | Out-File $LogFile -Append

Write-Log "Configuring UseAADCredentialType..."
reg add "HKLM\SOFTWARE\Policies\Microsoft\Windows\CurrentVersion\MDM" /v UseAADCredentialType /t REG_DWORD /d 1 /f 2>&1 | Out-File $LogFile -Append

Write-Log "Removing old scheduled task..."
schtasks /delete /tn "MDM AutoEnroll" /f 2>&1 | Out-File $LogFile -Append

$TaskTime = (Get-Date).AddMinutes(5).ToString("HH:mm")

Write-Log "Creating scheduled task for $TaskTime..."

$taskCmd = "$env:windir\system32\deviceenroller.exe /c /AutoEnrollMDM"

schtasks /create `
    /tn "MDM AutoEnroll" `
    /sc once `
    /st $TaskTime `
    /ru SYSTEM `
    /rl HIGHEST `
    /tr $taskCmd `
    /f 2>&1 | Out-File $LogFile -Append

Write-Log "Starting immediate enrollment..."

Start-Process "$env:windir\system32\deviceenroller.exe" `
    -ArgumentList "/c /AutoEnrollMDM" `
    -Wait

Write-Log "Enrollment command executed."

Write-Log "Dumping scheduled task info..."

schtasks /query /tn "MDM AutoEnroll" /v /fo LIST 2>&1 | Out-File $LogFile -Append

Write-Log "Script completed."
Write-Log "Log file located at $LogFile"


